main event: Unidentified flying objects were observed via radar and visually by military personnel over Sangley Point, Philippines on August 23, 1963.
interesting points: Radar detected 10 to 15 objects moving at speeds of 200 to 400 knots at altitudes between 35,000 ft and 50,000 ft,The objects disappeared and reappeared during the observation period,The visually reported speed of some objects exceeded 2,000 mph,Photos of the incidents were attempted, but the results were unknown,The objects were described as round and silver with an indistinct outline at approximately 4,000 feet.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects, possibly disc-like or round in shape
witness description: Military personnel and a pilot from Patrol Squadron Forty
